In SRS or SRS-like rotation systems, there is a widely-accepted (though non-standard) notation for describing the orientations of the blocks:

The original orientation of the block (the orientation of the block when the block is spawned) is denoted as "0";
The orientation of the block after a 90° clockwise (right) rotation is denoted as "R";
The orientation of the block after a 90° counterclockwise (left) rotation is denoted as "L";
The orientation of the block after a 180°  rotation is denoted as "2".

Under this system, 0→L means rotating counterclockwise from the original orientation (0) to L; 0→R means rotating clockwise from the original orientation (0) to R; 2→R means rotating counterclockwise from 2 (180°) to R.
